<a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=557.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: magic system</span><hr size=1> Oh good Grief - <br>
<br>
Midgarrd is a melee realm, Hibernia is a magic based realm, Albion is a mesh of the 2 with the most flexability in class veriety.<br>
<br>
I have a 60 Mage in EQ (Runestorm )and the comparisons of an Eldritch or a Bard (my 2 toons ) are not even close. No caster in any realm, or in EQ can claim as much flexability as the Hibernian Mentalist - bar none as an example.<br>
<br>
IMHO - the magc system is a LOT better in DAoC and balanced. Becasue at its core, is RvR - the classes just blows away anything else any game as done so far. In UO it was the tank/mage, in EQ you HAVE to HAVE a Enchanter/Cleric - or you do not even play unless you are a druid or Necro and into soloing. <br>
<br>
It comes down to being able to log in, group wtih friends and go and play. In DAoC the 'uber' encounters are set to 2 groups type of stuff, and both groups can get xp, yes for things like Dragons and Sea Monsters. In EQ it takes 30 + people = to 1 hour to just get organised, and that assumes you have the backing of 'raid mentality peeps'. And you do not get paid for being an Admin either :P<br>
<br>
I got 2 + years out of EQ (thanks EQ ), but play what you want. In the end, it is what will make you smile the most <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
